title: Match History not Loading

embed.description: The easy way to save screenshots, GIFs, and websites. Make everyone happy by sharing smarter, faster, and with your point crystal clear.

body: So, when I try to open my match history in my browser, it doesn't load. Please help me. (My browser is Microsoft Edge btw)

replies.body:
I'm seeing the same issue over here, regardless of whose profile I view. Waiting for friends in EUW, EUNE, and OCE to poke me about whether they're having the same issues viewing mine, or I'm having the same issues viewing theirs.

I attempted to load Twink3ys's match history in Firefox 50 (Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; Win64; x64; rv:50.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/50.0), using the Developer Tools (F12) immediately after clearing cache, and these were the error/warning lines I got. Times are UTC-6.

> 08:52:59.619 SyntaxError: expected expression, got end of script[Learn More]  twig.js:3625:21
> 08:53:02.318 Cross-Origin Request Blocked: The Same Origin Policy disallows reading the remote resource at http://status.leagueoflegends.com/shards/na/summary (Reason: CORS header ‘Access-Control-Allow-Origin’ does not match ‘(null)’).  (unknown)
> 08:53:03.182 GET https://riot-dradis-assets-oregon.s3.amazonaws.com/dradis-0.5.0-prod.min.js [HTTP/1.1 403 Forbidden 473ms]
> 08:53:03.844 ReferenceError: Dradis is not defined[Learn More]  analytics.min.js:4:8468
> 08:53:04.041 Cross-Origin Request Blocked: The Same Origin Policy disallows reading the remote resource at http://ddragon.leagueoflegends.com/cdn/6.24.1/js/dragonmagic.js (Reason: CORS header ‘Access-Control-Allow-Origin’ does not match ‘(null)’).
> 08:53:09.631 ReferenceError: Twig is not defined[Learn More]  ramen.js:24:21679

I have attempted to view both my own profile, and Twink3ys's profile, on Chrome and IE as well, with the same result. The respective browsers' dev tools produce much the same output.

Edit: I've conferred with a friend of mine in EUNE, and he states that he can view match histories -- including mine. On a lark, I changed "na" to "eune" in Porocles's link to Twink3ys's profile, and what do you know, [it works, at least for me](http://matchhistory.eune.leagueoflegends.com/en/#match-history/NA1/229736716). Interestingly, all the same errors/warnings are repeated on EUNE.

I was able to load up [your profile](http://matchhistory.na.leagueoflegends.com/en/#match-history/NA1/229736716) without any issues.  Try this on another browser or clearing your [cache ](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/201752694-Clearing-Browser-History-and-Cookies)to see if that helps.  Let me know if it helps!

it still doesn't work ;/

i tried clearing my cache and i'm using chrome

Hi, webdeveloper here, I have tracked it down myself to a truncated Twig.js file. I think maybe you guys got a bad push somewhere or something corrupted on a cdn. It seems you load theses assets off of S3, so maybe check your buckets.

http://matchhistory.na.leagueoflegends.com/assets/1.0.19/lib/twig.js

that's the link to the truncated JS in question.

Here is the remote IP that it's being resolved to: 104.16.139.241

Please fix. Let me know if you need more info.

Unfortunately, I don't know anything about web dev so this all looks like another language to me.  :P  I suggest posting this over at the[ bug boards ](http://boards.na.leagueoflegends.com/en/c/bug-report) if you're seeing an issue so more knowledgeable parties can review it.  Thanks for the help!
